hopobject.body: Children with disabilities sante-medecine.journaldesfemmes.com Meetings in Bremerhaven have been held to establish reserves which ban fishing and protect species including seals and penguins. If successful the plans would more than double the area of the world’s oceans that are protected. The proposed protected zone in the Ross Sea has drawn much interest due to it being the home to a large proportion of the world’s Adelie penguins.
